  <!-- ======= 9. 05 Voice & Tone ======= -->
  <section class="slide" id="slide-9">
    <div class="slide__inner">
      <p class="km-section-num reveal">05</p>
      <h2 class="slide__heading reveal">Voice &amp; Tone</h2>
      <p class="km-section-intro fade-in">Korman's voice is the mechanic who hands you the keys after a rebuild and says "drive it hard, that's what it's for." Knowledgeable, direct, warm underneath. Never shouts. Never oversells. The work speaks.</p>

      <div class="km-voice-grid stagger-children">
        <div class="km-voice km-voice--do"><div class="km-voice__label">Do</div><p class="km-voice__text">"Stage II adds 18 horsepower and moves the torque peak 400rpm lower. You'll feel it exiting every corner."</p></div>
        <div class="km-voice km-voice--dont"><div class="km-voice__label">Don't</div><p class="km-voice__text">"Our INCREDIBLE Stage II package delivers INSANE power gains for the ULTIMATE driving experience!!!"</p></div>
        <div class="km-voice km-voice--do"><div class="km-voice__label">Do</div><p class="km-voice__text">"This engine has 180,000 miles on it. The bearings look like the day they were installed. That's what happens when you break it in right."</p></div>
        <div class="km-voice km-voice--dont"><div class="km-voice__label">Don't</div><p class="km-voice__text">"Trust the experts at Korman Autoworks for all your BMW needs! We're passionate about performance!"</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="km-card-grid km-card-grid--3 stagger-children">
        <div class="km-rule"><div class="km-rule__title">Show the work</div><div class="km-rule__text">Dyno sheets, not adjectives. Race results, not testimonials. Part numbers, not promises. Let the evidence do the talking.</div></div>
        <div class="km-rule"><div class="km-rule__title">Respect the car</div><div class="km-rule__text">Never talk down about stock BMWs. Korman improves them. The car deserved better from the factory&mdash;that's why we're here.</div></div>
        <div class="km-rule"><div class="km-rule__title">Quiet confidence</div><div class="km-rule__text">Two Watkins Glen wins. IMSA championships. Lotus, Datsun, BMW. We don't lead with credentials&mdash;but they're there when you look.</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 10. 06 Pedigree — Network ======= -->
  <section class="slide" id="slide-10">
    <div class="slide__inner">
      <p class="km-section-num reveal">06</p>
      <h2 class="slide__heading reveal">Motorsport Pedigree</h2>
      <p class="km-section-intro fade-in">Korman Autoworks didn't develop in isolation. The shop sits at the intersection of three lines of top-tier motorsport engineering&mdash;connections that would be equivalent to F1 pedigree today.</p>

      <div class="km-label">The Knowledge Network</div>
      <div class="stagger-children">
        <div class="km-net">
          <div class="km-net__title">Heidegger AG</div>
          <div class="km-net__sub">Formula 2 Engines · Le Mans · Liechtenstein</div>
          <p class="km-net__text">Max Heidegger specialized in BMW race cars and Formula 2 engines. At the 1975 24 Hours of Le Mans, a Heidegger-prepared BMW 2002 with an F2-spec engine&mdash;260hp at 8,500rpm, 1,000kg&mdash;won its class outright.</p>
          <div class="km-net__conn"><strong>Korman connection:</strong> Korman's competition department trained at Heidegger AG directly. Following that training, the shop built BMW F2 and M1 engines in Greensboro. <span class="rk">RK &mdash; Who trained, when, how long?</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="km-net">
          <div class="km-net__title">Corky Bell</div>
          <div class="km-net__sub">Cartech Racing · Maximum Boost · SCCA/IMSA</div>
          <p class="km-net__text">Courtland "Corky" Bell. ME from Texas A&amp;M, 12 years at Bell Helicopter. Founded Cartech Racing (1977). Author of <em>Maximum Boost</em>&mdash;the definitive turbocharging text, still in print.</p>
          <div class="km-net__conn"><strong>Korman connection:</strong> Direct collaboration on twin turbo M30/633 kits (20 made, Bell factory fire destroyed all tooling). Also consulted on Korman's 2002 Turbo rebuild. <span class="rk">RK &mdash; Broader collaboration scope?</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="km-net">
          <div class="km-net__title">Gerhard Schruf</div>
          <div class="km-net__sub">Brown Boveri · Ferrari F1 · Bell Intercoolers</div>
          <p class="km-net__text">Bell's engineering partner. Instrumental in developing the COMPREX pressure-wave supercharger at Brown Boveri. Provided forced induction expertise to Scuderia Ferrari&mdash;the 126CX tested by Villeneuve and Pironi.</p>
          <div class="km-net__conn"><strong>Korman connection:</strong> Through Bell partnership. When Korman collaborated with Bell on turbo development, the technical depth included Schruf's F1-grade forced induction expertise. <span class="rk">RK &mdash; Direct contact with Schruf?</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="km-net km-net--highlight">
          <div class="km-net__title">BMW NA Motorsport</div>
          <div class="km-net__sub">Factory Relationship · Direct</div>
          <p class="km-net__text">Erik Wensberg, BMW North America Motorsports Manager: <em>"We chose Ray Korman to run the M3&hellip;more for his expertise in new car development, especially BMW development. That's his real forte."</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

