  <!-- ======= 14. 08 Design Principles ======= -->
  <section class="slide" id="slide-14">
    <div class="slide__inner">
      <p class="km-section-num reveal">08</p>
      <h2 class="slide__heading reveal">Design Principles</h2>
      <p class="km-section-intro fade-in">Every design choice should pass the shop-floor test: would this look right hand-painted on a garage wall, stamped on an intake manifold, or printed on a timing sheet?</p>

      <div class="km-card-grid km-card-grid--3 stagger-children" style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
        <div class="km-rule"><div class="km-rule__title">Heritage form, modern execution</div><div class="km-rule__text">Classic shapes&mdash;the roundel, the stripe, the condensed sans&mdash;built with contemporary precision. The Heist principle applied to motorsport.</div></div>
        <div class="km-rule"><div class="km-rule__title">Patina is proof</div><div class="km-rule__text">Texture, grain, and wear are welcome. A logo that looks better scuffed into a toolbox lid than printed on a business card is the right logo.</div></div>
        <div class="km-rule"><div class="km-rule__title">Let the cars be the color</div><div class="km-rule__text">The brand system is deliberately restrained&mdash;warm neutrals, blue accent, red sparingly&mdash;because the BMWs themselves provide the color. Alpina Green, Dakar Yellow, Henna Red.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="km-card-grid km-card-grid--3 stagger-children">
        <div class="km-rule"><div class="km-rule__title">Technical, not corporate</div><div class="km-rule__text">Part numbers over taglines. Dyno charts over hero images. Specifications over descriptions. The brand communicates like an engineer's notebook.</div></div>
        <div class="km-rule"><div class="km-rule__title">Condensed is confident</div><div class="km-rule__text">Barlow Condensed at heavy weights is the visual signature. It takes up less space because it doesn't need to shout&mdash;the weight does the talking.</div></div>
        <div class="km-rule"><div class="km-rule__title">The stripe earns its place</div><div class="km-rule__text">The M-stripe is a mark of motorsport legitimacy, not decoration. Use it once per layout, at the top or as a divider. Never as a pattern.</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

